title: "FHA Unified Database: Replication Package for Displacing Deference"
authors:
  - family-names: Gill
    given-names: Nicholas
    email: "nickgill@arizona.edu"
    affiliation: "J.D. Candidate, 2027, University of Arizona James E. Rogers College of Law"
type: dataset
date-released: 2026-04-01
url: "https://github.com/NickGillArizona/Displacing-Deference-Data-and-Doctrine-for-a-Disability-Centered-AFFH"
repository-code: "https://github.com/NickGillArizona/Displacing-Deference-Data-and-Doctrine-for-a-Disability-Centered-AFFH"
abstract: >-
  Replication package for a Note arguing that AFFH's present problem is a
  durability failure, that disability exposes it most clearly, and that
  the reinforcement/replication distinction supplies a limiting principle.
  Contains the FHA Unified Database (2,522 screened-in federal FHA cases;
  1,770 disability), race-by-disability housing cost-burden
  cross-tabulations, HUD administrative-system analyses (CDBG, REAC/NSPIRE,
  POSH), classification pipeline documentation, and supplementary appendices.
keywords:
  - fair housing act
  - disability
  - AFFH
  - administrative law
  - HUD
  - empirical legal studies
  - LLM classification
  - housing cost burden
  - replication package
  - census pums
